## 11. Test Impact & Potential Failures

### Button Tests
- [ ] Tests looking for `aria-disabled` may fail — `isDisabled` now sets `disabled` (not `aria-disabled`) for standard buttons
- [ ] `aria-disabled` only renders when `true`
- [ ] RTL `byText` queries return the text wrapper `<span>`, not the `<button>` — use `byRole('button', { name: '...' })` instead

### Select Tests
- [ ] RTL queries may not find menu options if Popper sets `aria-disabled` after selection
- [ ] Fix: Pass `{hidden: true}` option or set `appendTo="inline"`

### General Test Updates
- [ ] Update snapshot tests for new markup (many components have structural changes)
- [ ] Update CSS class assertions: `pf-v5-*` → `pf-v6-*`
- [ ] Update OUIA component type assertions: `PF5/` → `PF6/`

---

## 12. Upgrade Steps Summary

1. **Update all dependencies** to PF6 versions in `package.json`
2. **Run codemods** (before any manual changes):
   ```bash
   npx @patternfly/pf-codemods@latest <src> --v6        # dry run
   npx @patternfly/pf-codemods@latest <src> --v6 --fix  # apply fixes
   npx @patternfly/pf-codemods@latest <src> --v6 --fix --only data-codemods-cleanup  # cleanup
   ```
3. **Run class-name-updater** (with `--v6 --fix`):
   - Replaces `pf-v5` CSS class prefixes with `pf-v6`
4. **Run tokens-update** (part of main codemods):
   - Updates global CSS variables and React tokens
   - Flags unresolvable tokens with hot pink color
5. **Run css-vars-updater** for non-React files (`.css`, `.scss`, `.md`)
6. **Remove/update CSS overrides**:
   - Temporarily remove overrides, check appearance
   - Remove overrides that no longer apply
   - Update remaining overrides to use new design tokens
7. **Update breakpoint logic** (px → rem)
8. **Manual review** of flagged issues (especially EmptyState, Modal)
9. **Update tests** (button queries, snapshot tests, CSS class assertions)
10. **Build and verify**

---

