<section id="detailed-analysis">
<h2>🔍 Detailed Analysis</h2>

<!-- Package Upgrades -->
<details id="pkg-upgrades">
  <summary>📦 Package Upgrades <span class="badge badge-green" style="margin-left:auto">Winner: pf-codemods</span></summary>
  <div class="details-body">
    <h4>What PF6 requires</h4>
    <p>The base branch is <strong>already on PF6 packages</strong>: <code>@patternfly/react-core: ~6.4.0</code>, <code>@patternfly/react-icons: ~6.4.0</code>, <code>@patternfly/react-table: ~6.4.0</code>, <code>@patternfly/react-topology: ~6.4.0</code>. No PatternFly package version changes are needed.</p>

    <table class="comparison-mini">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Aspect</th><th>pf-codemods</th><th>semver/goose</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>PatternFly packages</td>
          <td class="winner-cell">No change needed ✅</td>
          <td class="winner-cell">No change needed ✅</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>package.json modified</td>
          <td class="winner-cell">No (correct) ✅</td>
          <td class="loser-cell">Yes — 12 non-PF packages changed ❌</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>React version</td>
          <td class="winner-cell">17.0.2 (unchanged) ✅</td>
          <td class="loser-cell">→ ^18.3.1 (unnecessary, breaks webpack) ❌</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>react-router</td>
          <td class="winner-cell">5.3.x (unchanged) ✅</td>
          <td class="loser-cell">→ ^7.16.0 (unnecessary, breaks webpack) ❌</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>react-i18next</td>
          <td class="winner-cell">^11.7.3 (unchanged) ✅</td>
          <td class="loser-cell">→ ^2.2.3 (DOWNGRADE! breaks webpack) ❌</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>use-immer</td>
          <td class="winner-cell">^0.8.1 (unchanged) ✅</td>
          <td class="loser-cell">→ ^0.1.0 (DOWNGRADE! causes 16 TS errors) ❌</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <div class="highlight-box">
      <strong>Critical issue in semver/goose:</strong> The branch changes <code>react-i18next</code> from <code>^11.7.3</code> to <code>^2.2.3</code> — this is a <strong>massive downgrade</strong> from v11 to v2. Similarly, <code>use-immer</code> goes from <code>^0.8.1</code> to <code>^0.1.0</code>. These are version regressions, not upgrades. The <code>react-router</code> jump from 5.3 to 7.16 is also not required for PF6 migration and breaks the OpenShift Console plugin SDK's shared module validation.
    </div>

    <p>None of these dependency changes are required for PatternFly 6. PF6 is compatible with React 17+ and does not require React 18, react-router 7, or any of the other changes made.</p>

    <div class="winner-badge">🏆 Winner: pf-codemods — correctly left packages unchanged</div>
  </div>
</details>

<!-- Modal Migration -->
<details id="modal-migration">
  <summary>🪟 Modal Migration <span class="badge badge-orange" style="margin-left:auto">Winner: Neither (both wrong)</span></summary>
  <div class="details-body">
    <h4>What PF6 requires</h4>
    <p>PF6 has two Modal APIs:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>New composable Modal</strong> (promoted from <code>/next</code>) — at <code>@patternfly/react-core</code>: uses <code>&lt;Modal&gt;</code> + <code>&lt;ModalHeader&gt;</code> + <code>&lt;ModalBody&gt;</code> + <code>&lt;ModalFooter&gt;</code></li>
      <li><strong>Old deprecated Modal</strong> — at <code>@patternfly/react-core/deprecated</code>: uses <code>&lt;Modal title="..." actions={...}&gt;</code></li>
    </ul>

    <div class="highlight-box info">
      <strong>Key finding:</strong> The base branch already uses the <strong>new composable Modal API</strong> correctly. <code>NodeSelectorModal.tsx</code> uses <code>&lt;Modal isOpen variant={ModalVariant.small}&gt;&lt;ModalHeader/&gt;&lt;ModalBody/&gt;&lt;ModalFooter/&gt;&lt;/Modal&gt;</code> — this is the <em>new</em> PF6 pattern imported from main <code>@patternfly/react-core</code>.
    </div>

    <h4>Before (main branch — already correct)</h4>
    <pre><code><span class="code-add">import { ModalBody, ModalFooter, ModalHeader } from '@patternfly/react-core';</span>
<span class="code-add">import { Modal, ModalVariant } from '@patternfly/react-core'; // new composable API</span>

&lt;Modal onClose={onClose} isOpen={isOpen} variant={ModalVariant.small}&gt;
  &lt;ModalHeader title={t('Node Selector')} /&gt;
  &lt;ModalBody&gt;...&lt;/ModalBody&gt;
  &lt;ModalFooter&gt;...&lt;/ModalFooter&gt;
&lt;/Modal&gt;</code></pre>

    <table class="comparison-mini">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Aspect</th><th>pf-codemods</th><th>semver/goose</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>What it did</td>
          <td class="loser-cell">Moved Modal to <code>/deprecated</code> import ❌</td>
          <td class="winner-cell">Left Modal imports unchanged ✅</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Correctness</td>
          <td class="loser-cell">WRONG — moves new API to deprecated path</td>
          <td class="winner-cell">Correct — keeps new API in main path</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Impact</td>
          <td class="loser-cell">8 files now import from wrong path. Will use old Modal class, causing prop mismatches with ModalHeader/ModalBody/ModalFooter usage.</td>
          <td class="winner-cell">No change, no regression.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h4>pf-codemods after (WRONG)</h4>
    <pre><code><span class="code-del">import { Modal } from '@patternfly/react-core/deprecated'; // WRONG! This is the OLD deprecated Modal</span>
<span class="code-add">import { ModalBody, ModalFooter, ModalHeader } from '@patternfly/react-core'; // These are NEW API</span>

// Now using OLD deprecated Modal shell with NEW composable children — API MISMATCH!</code></pre>

    <div class="highlight-box">
      <strong>pf-codemods error:</strong> The codemod tool blindly moved <code>Modal</code> to <code>/deprecated</code> without recognizing that the code was already using the <em>new</em> composable Modal API. This creates an API mismatch: the deprecated Modal has <code>title</code>, <code>actions</code>, <code>footer</code> props but does NOT compose with separate <code>ModalHeader</code>/<code>ModalBody</code>/<code>ModalFooter</code> children from the new API.
    </div>

    <div class="tie-badge">⚖️ Neither wins cleanly — pf-codemods makes it worse, semver/goose does nothing</div>
  </div>
</details>

<!-- PageSection -->
<details id="pagesection">
  <summary>📄 PageSection / PageBreadcrumb <span class="badge badge-green" style="margin-left:auto">Winner: pf-codemods</span></summary>
  <div class="details-body">
    <h4>What PF6 requires</h4>
    <p>Per the official PF6 upgrade guide, <code>PageSection</code> and <code>PageBreadcrumb</code> now default to <code>hasBodyWrapper={true}</code>. To match PF5 behavior (no body wrapper), you should add <code>hasBodyWrapper={false}</code> explicitly. This is documented in the <code>pageBreadcrumbAndSection-warn-updated-wrapperLogic</code> codemod rule.</p>

    <table class="comparison-mini">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Aspect</th><th>pf-codemods</th><th>semver/goose</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>PageSection hasBodyWrapper added</td>
          <td class="winner-cell">Yes — 9 instances across 7 files ✅</td>
          <td class="loser-cell">No — not addressed ❌</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>PageBreadcrumb hasBodyWrapper added</td>
          <td class="winner-cell">Yes — 1 instance ✅</td>
          <td class="loser-cell">No — not addressed ❌</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Correctness</td>
          <td class="winner-cell">Correct per PF6 docs ✅</td>
          <td>N/A</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h4>Example change (pf-codemods — correct)</h4>
    <pre><code><span class="code-del">- &lt;PageBreadcrumb&gt;{breadcrumb}&lt;/PageBreadcrumb&gt;</span>
<span class="code-add">+ &lt;PageBreadcrumb hasBodyWrapper={false}&gt;{breadcrumb}&lt;/PageBreadcrumb&gt;</span>

<span class="code-del">- &lt;PageSection&gt;</span>
<span class="code-add">+ &lt;PageSection hasBodyWrapper={false}&gt;</span></code></pre>

    <p>Branch 2 (semver/goose) does <em>not</em> add <code>hasBodyWrapper={false}</code> to any PageSection or PageBreadcrumb. However, it wraps some <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> containers with <code>&lt;Page&gt;</code> — which is a different (questionable) change.</p>

    <div class="winner-badge">🏆 Winner: pf-codemods — addresses PF6 PageSection change correctly</div>
  </div>
</details>

