<!-- Layout Components -->
<details id="layout-components">
  <summary>⚠️ Layout Components (StackItem, SplitItem) <span class="badge badge-red" style="margin-left:auto">CRITICAL: semver/goose introduces runtime crashes</span></summary>
  <div class="details-body">
    <h4>What PF6 requires</h4>
    <p><code>StackItem</code> and <code>SplitItem</code> have a <code>component</code> prop that sets the <strong>HTML element type</strong> to render (defaults to <code>'div'</code>). It expects a <strong>string</strong> like <code>'div'</code>, <code>'span'</code>, <code>'section'</code> — NOT a React element.</p>

    <h4>PF6 Source Code (authoritative)</h4>
    <pre><code>// @patternfly/react-core/src/layouts/Stack/StackItem.tsx
export const StackItem = ({
  component = 'div',  // ← DEFAULT IS STRING 'div'
  ...props
}) => {
  const Component = component as any;
  return &lt;Component {...props}&gt;{children}&lt;/Component&gt;;  // ← USED AS ELEMENT TYPE
};</code></pre>

    <div class="highlight-box">
      <strong>CRITICAL BUG in semver/goose:</strong> Branch 2 passes JSX <em>elements</em> (React nodes) to the <code>component</code> prop instead of element type strings. This pattern will <strong>crash at runtime</strong> because React cannot use a rendered element as a component constructor. There are <strong>20+ instances</strong> of this pattern across ~10 files.
    </div>

    <h4>semver/goose pattern (WRONG — will crash)</h4>
    <pre><code><span class="code-del">// BEFORE (correct — children as content)
&lt;StackItem&gt;
  &lt;Radio id="..." label="..." /&gt;
&lt;/StackItem&gt;</span>

<span class="code-del">// AFTER in semver/goose (WRONG — JSX element as component type)
&lt;StackItem component={&lt;Radio id="..." label="..." /&gt;} /&gt;</span>

// What component prop actually expects:
&lt;StackItem component="span"&gt;  {/* ← string element type */}
  &lt;Radio id="..." label="..." /&gt;
&lt;/StackItem&gt;</code></pre>

    <h4>Affected files in semver/goose (partial list)</h4>
    <ul>
      <li><code>ListSkeleton.tsx</code> — 4 instances of <code>&lt;StackItem component={&lt;Skeleton .../&gt;} /&gt;</code></li>
      <li><code>NodeSelectionRadioGroup.tsx</code> — 4 instances with Radio and EditButton</li>
      <li><code>UplinkConnectionStep.tsx</code> — 3 instances with Radio</li>
      <li><code>PolicyEnactments.tsx</code> — 4 instances with icon elements</li>
      <li><code>NeighborInformations.tsx</code> — 5 instances with text/JSX content</li>
      <li><code>EnactmentStateTab.tsx</code> — 2 SplitItem instances</li>
      <li><code>SearchBar.tsx</code> — 2 SplitItem instances</li>
    </ul>

    <table class="comparison-mini">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Aspect</th><th>pf-codemods</th><th>semver/goose</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>StackItem/SplitItem changes</td>
          <td class="winner-cell">None (left as-is) ✅</td>
          <td class="loser-cell">20+ incorrect changes ❌</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Runtime impact</td>
          <td class="winner-cell">No regression ✅</td>
          <td class="loser-cell">CRASH — React can't render JSX element as component type ❌</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <div class="winner-badge">🏆 Winner: pf-codemods — did not introduce this critical bug</div>
  </div>
</details>

<!-- Button Icon Prop -->
<details id="button-icon">
  <summary>🔘 Button Icon Prop Migration <span class="badge badge-green" style="margin-left:auto">Winner: semver/goose</span></summary>
  <div class="details-body">
    <h4>What PF6 requires</h4>
    <p>Per PF6 migration guide (<code>button-moveIcons-icon-prop</code> codemod rule): icons should be passed to the <code>icon</code> prop instead of as children, especially for <code>variant="plain"</code> buttons. Button text is now wrapped in a <code>&lt;span class="pf-v6-c-button__text"&gt;</code>.</p>

    <table class="comparison-mini">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Aspect</th><th>pf-codemods</th><th>semver/goose</th></tr>
